The paper focuses on optimizing mobile applications, which falls under the category of mobile computing (cs.MOBILE). The proposed technique involves iterative compilation, which is a common technique used in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the capture and replay technique, which is commonly used in software engineering for debugging and testing (cs.SE). The paper involves optimizing the performance of mobile applications, which can be considered a systems problem (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of adapting optimization strategies for mobile devices, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR).
